    "title": "Making camera actions available to Siri and Apple Intelligence"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To integrate your app’s camera capabilities with Siri and Apple Intelligence, you use Swift macros that generate additional",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "properties and add protocol conformance for your app intent and app enumeration implementation that Apple Intelligence needs. For example, if your app allows a person to take a photo or video, use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantIntent(schema:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " macro and provide the assistant schema",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that consists of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".camera",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " domain and the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantSchemas/CameraIntent/startCapture",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " schema:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "@AssistantIntent(schema: .camera.startCapture)",
            "struct StartCaptureIntent {",
            "    var captureMode: CaptureMode",
            "    var timerDuration: CaptureDuration?",
            "    var device: CaptureDevice?",
            "",
            "    func perform() async throws -> some IntentResult {",
            "        .result()",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To learn more about assistant schemas, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/Integrating-actions-with-siri-and-apple-intelligence",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For a list of available app intents in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".camera",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " domain, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantSchemas/CameraIntent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Make-sure-your-enumeration-meets-requirements",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Make sure your enumeration meets requirements",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To make sure Siri and Apple Intelligence understand custom static types for your intent parameters,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "annotate app enumerations with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantEnum(schema:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " macro. Then, pass the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".camera",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " domain",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and a schema to it. The following example uses the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantSchemas/CameraEnum/captureMode",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " schema:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "@AssistantEnum(schema: .camera.captureMode)",
            "struct CameraCaptureMode: String, AppEnum {",
            "    // Your app's camera capture modes.",
            "    case portrait",
            "    case landscape",
            "    case catFace",
            "    case awesomeFilter",
            "",
            "    static var caseDisplayRepresentations: [ClearHistoryTimeFrame: DisplayRepresentation] = [:]",
            "",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For a list of available app enumeration schemas in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".camera",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " domain, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/AssistantSchemas/CameraEnum",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
